        "award_amount": 1079698.0,
        "description": "The interplanetary network (IPN) is a consortium of space-based high-energy monitors who together detect  localize  and characterize short-duration high-energy transients. The ipn was key to discovering magnetars  enabled the use of the james webb space telescope for direct proof of heavy element nucleosynthesis  and has provided continuous  all-sky monitoring of the high-energy sky for decades. However  the operations of the ipn are outdated. We propose to modernize and automate the ipn operations  to broaden its scope  and to create key infrastructure for the global time-domain and multimessage astrophysics ecosystem. These efforts will be focused on gamma-ray bursts  being the most luminous events in the universe since the big bang.",
